  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "As of now, the pod network container is susceptible to OOM kills due to system memory pressure. By setting the oom_score_adj to be a value lesser than '0', which is the default for docker containers, we can protect the network container. There are a couple of ways to solve this.\n\nIn the short term, we will have the kubelet update the oom_score_adj of the network container's 'pause' process after the container gets created by docker. This approach is not robust, but this will help alleviate the current state of the node.\n\nAfter this, we will investigate either using a docker pre-start hook (cc @vmarmol) or expose a 'oom_score' option in docker, to apply oom scores.\n\nHaving memory limits set on all containers will be a better long term solution. But until we get there, the above mentioned solutions will keep the node stable.\n\ncc @dchen1107 @rjnagal @bgrant0607 \n",
